(0, 0), (A, B), (2A, 2B), (3A, 3B), \ldots \pmod{n}
A,B,n \leq 10000
(\Rightarrow)\ 
\rm\:z = aB-bA.\:
\rm\:ax+by\equiv 0\ \:\Rightarrow\ xz,\:yz\equiv 0 \ \Rightarrow\ z \equiv (x,y)z\equiv 0
\rm\:xz,yz\equiv 0\ \Rightarrow z \equiv (ix+jy)z\equiv i(xz)+j(yz)\equiv 0\pmod n
\rm\ \ ord(z)\ |\ x,y\ \Rightarrow\ ord(z)\ |\ (x,y) = 1\ 
\rm\:(\mathbb Z/n,+)
